Package: eDNAstructure
Title: Dirichlet-Multinomial Mixture Models for eDNA Metabarcoding Community Structure
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Pedro", "Brandao-Dias", email = "pbdfp@uw.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Fits Bayesian Dirichlet-Multinomial Mixture (DMM) models to
    environmental DNA (eDNA) read count data from metabarcoding surveys. The model
    identifies latent ecological communities, estimates their taxonomic compositions,
    and quantifies how environmental covariates (e.g., depth, latitude) drive
    community membership. Stan is used for posterior inference. Visualization
    functions produce publication-ready ggplot2 objects for community structure
    plots, NMDS ordinations, and covariate coefficient plots.
